<DOC><DOCNO> AP900706-0149 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-06-90 1748EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-PlantExplosion-Quotes     07-06 0246</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Plant Explosion-Quotes,0256</SECOND><HEAD>With AM-Plant Explosion, Bjt</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   The explosion that leveled an area the size of a city block atthe Arco Chemical Co. plant Thursday night in Channelview, Texas,was heard twenty miles away.   Here are some quotes from plant workers and others:</TEXT><TEXT>   ``We heard the explosion and started running,'' said MarleneFiscus, who was working for a cleaning service at the plant.   ``There was black smoke and flames in the unit right behind us.Had we been another 10 feet back, the explosion would have blown usaway.''</TEXT><TEXT>   ``I seen a big flash cross in front of my eyes. I looked over tomy left and I saw a big ball of fire. It looked to me like a tankrun off, you know, like a rocket just took off,'' said Mike Zugel,a truck driver.</TEXT><TEXT>   ``I saw a circular red flash like an atomic bomb went off. Thelights flickered, and then I heard a loud explosion,'' said GlennDickey Jr., who lives about a mile from the plant.</TEXT><TEXT>   ``In my 32 years with Arco Chemical Company, I can't rememberany single accident of this dimension where we've had multiple lossof life to the extent we had here,'' said Jack Johnson, presidentof Arco Chemical of North America. ``It certainly is a time thatall of the employees and myself grieve the loss of fellowemployees. One loss of life is not acceptable.''</TEXT></DOC>